# Documentation Governance

SaleOS Docs is the **canonical** product narrative. A platform change is **not complete** until Docs, code, and tests are updated together.

## Same-PR rule

When documenting or changing processes for any feature, fix, enhancement, architecture, config, deployment, migration, permission, API, CI/CD, or operational change:

1. Update the affected VitePress pages in **this same PR**.
2. Update `/changelog/` delivery notes (and release pages under `/changelog/vX.Y.Z-platform` when cutting a platform release).
3. Keep cross-links (User Guide ↔ Developer Guide ↔ Deployment ↔ API) consistent.
4. Do **not** claim git tags or CI results that were not verified.

Canonical page: `docs/developer-guide/documentation-governance.md`.

## Coverage matrix

Keep synchronized when relevant: Product Roadmap, Changelog, Architecture, Developer Guides, API, Deployment, Upgrade, Runbooks, Env/Config, Permissions, Testing, CI/CD, Release Process.

## Non-negotiables

- Respect platform freeze — no parallel foundation redesign docs.
- Prefer migrate-only production guidance (no `db:seed` in upgrade paths).
- Dead links fail the Docs Quality Gate (`ignoreDeadLinks: false`).
